commitResults.messageTitle: UI refactor for v1.2, first edition
commitResults.messageBody:
Added in avatars, refactor the overall layout.

File edited include DarkTheme.css, MainWindow.fxml, PersonListPanel.fxml, ResultDisplay.fxml

Added in avatar for student list, will loop the image every 9 times.
Added in icon to better differentiate the information.
Changed the help display.
Make the text wrap when too long.

Fulfil the basic requirement about check.
Now key in check + index number, the respective student will be highlighted.

Part that related with task and score will be implemented after other
teammates complete the functions.

Additional modify need to be made, including realtime update and
focus scroll (if possible).

Listview scrollTo is inaccurate, change the implementation approach
The user can check for one student's information, meanwhile, instead
of display the entire list, will only display the checked student.

Modified to UI to resolve problem, when the number of cell
is not enough, the background will auto filled with the empty list
view with background color. Change them to transparent.
Added in four different test cases for check command
Added in the test for check command parser.

The previous check is based on the existing NameContainsKeywordsPredicate,
however, the behind logic is to use any match, which defeat the purpose of check
as the intended behaviour should be all match.

Therefore, the code is now changed to all match (as we will not have people with exact
same name, only one person can be selected each time).
Removed three unused import.

commitResults.messageTitle: Resolve the cut text problem and UI refinement
commitResults.messageBody: Solved the cut text issue and refine the current UI.

The avatar now is assigned based on the
gender tag given. If both gender is provided, deemed
as unisex.

Added score bar in case width is small

Delete will set task and score list to unchecked state

The task list and score list will reset
to unchecked status only if the deleted student
is also the current checked student.

Previously did not consider the condition that the checkPerson
is null. Fixed it by adding more restriction. All the tests can
pass now.
Fixed the image path issue

Added logging information to CheckCommend to
detect the exceeding student index during check

between graph and list based on their liking.

will add in CLI option later.

hover over a certain node, the respective information
will be displayed, including exam label and exact mark.

User can key in "switch" to trigger tab switch instead of click the tab.

Test if nested branch work as expected.

Make the UI more responsive.

1. Except score chart, everything is scrollable both vertically and horizontally.
2. Adjust all padding and font size.
3. Score chart is now scrollable.
4. When checked, the list will not show the checked student only
5. Add in text wrap and make sure the text display normal even in extreme case.
6. In case text in tooltip is too long, restrict the display to 12 characters,
anything more than that will be displayed as ellipsis
7. Change the check behaviour, when a student is being edited, the check
will go back to "no one is being checked" state.

1. In case the user name is super long, which might affect
the behaviour when window size is super small. If the name is
more than 30 letters, the following will show as ellipsis
2. The first time user open the application, it will detect the window
size and the default display will be the window size - 100px.
